Installation¶

  • install Julia 0.5 as described in http://julialang.org/downloads/
  • start the Julia REPL in your favorite terminal
  • run Pkg.clone("https://github.com/SimonDanisch/MIT18065.git")
  • run Pkg.test("MIT18065")
  • it will open a web browser where you can select getting started.ipynb which will lead you to this notebook
  • if anything doesn't work, please check the output in the REPL, it will contain information on fixing issues.

Getting started¶

Any script you run should include using MIT18065 at the top

this will ensure, that all needed functionality is available.

Overlaying plots in one window¶

In [5]:
# only plot points
p4 = scatter(s) 
# plot points with a different shape
# plotting functions ending in ! will append to the plot in the first argument
pλ = scatter!(p4, λ, m = :rect)
Out[5]:

Combining different plots in one window and adding titles and axes¶

In [6]:
p2 = spy(U'U, title = "U'U")
p3 = spy(V'V, xaxis = "x", yaxis = "y")
plot(p1, p2, p3, pλ)
Out[6]:

### You can include julia files with functions in the following way:
In [9]:
path = demopath("testfunction.jl")
println(path) # display it just to check where it is on your PC
# read in the file, just to see what kind of function it is
println(open(readstring, path))

/home/s/.julia/v0.5/MIT18065/demos/testfunction.jl
function testfunction(A)
    s = svdvals(A)
    U, S, V = svd(A)
    λ = eigvals(A)
    p1 = spy(-A)
    p2 = spy(U'U)
    p3 = spy(V'V)
    p4 = plot(s, m = :circle)
    plot(p1, p2, p3, p4)
end
In [10]:
include(path) # include the actual file with testfunction
# call testfunction
testfunction(rand(3, 3))
